President Biden recently held a meeting with White House Senior Advisors and outside experts to discuss voting rights in America. They focused on anti-voter legislation proposed or passed by state legislatures, pending legislation before Congress, and recent actions taken by the Department of Justice to protect voting rights. The President emphasized the Administration's commitment to working with Congress to pass important legislation and increasing engagement with the public on voting rights. He also reaffirmed his strong determination to protect the right to vote in free and fair elections.